{"name": "aioconsole", "metadata": {"name": "aioconsole", "version": "0.5.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vxgmichel/aioconsole", "license": "GPLv3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Asynchronous console and interfaces for asyncio", "upload_time": 1661865515}, "documentation": ["# aioconsole\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/aioconsole/badge/?version=latest\n:alt: true\n:target: http://aioconsole.readthedocs.io/\n```\n\n```{image} https://github.com/vxgmichel/aioconsole/workflows/CI/badge.svg\n:alt: true\n:target: https://github.com/vxgmichel/aioconsole/actions?query=branch%3Amaster\n```\n\n```{image} https://codecov.io/gh/vxgmichel/aioconsole/branch/master/graph/badge.svg\n:alt: true\n:target: https://codecov.io/gh/vxgmichel/aioconsole\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/aioconsole.svg\n:alt: true\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aioconsole\n```\n\n```{image} https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/aioconsole.svg\n:alt: true\n:target: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aioconsole\n```\n\nAsynchronous console and interfaces for asyncio\n\n[aioconsole] provides:\n\n- asynchronous equivalents to [input], [print], [exec] and [code.interact]\n- an interactive loop running the asynchronous python console\n- a way to customize and run command line interface using [argparse]\n- [stream] support to serve interfaces instead of using standard streams\n- the `apython` script to access asyncio code at runtime without modifying the sources\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Python >= 3.6\n\n## Installation\n\n[aioconsole] is available on [PyPI] and [GitHub].\nBoth of the following commands install the `aioconsole` package\nand the `apython` script.\n\n```console\n$ pip3 install aioconsole   # from PyPI\n$ python3 setup.py install  # or from the sources\n$ apython -h\nusage: apython [-h] [--serve [HOST:] PORT] [--no-readline]\n               [--banner BANNER] [--locals LOCALS]\n               [-m MODULE | FILE] ...\n\nRun the given python file or module with a modified asyncio policy replacing\nthe default event loop with an interactive loop. If no argument is given, it\nsimply runs an asynchronous python console.\n\npositional arguments:\n  FILE                  python file to run\n  ARGS                  extra arguments\n\noptional arguments:\n  -h, --help            show this help message and exit\n  --serve [HOST:] PORT, -s [HOST:] PORT\n                        serve a console on the given interface instead\n  --no-readline         force readline disabling\n  --banner BANNER       provide a custom banner\n  --locals LOCALS       provide custom locals as a dictionary\n  -m MODULE             run a python module\n```\n\n## Simple usage\n\nThe following example demonstrates the use of `await` inside the console:\n\n```console\n$ apython\nPython 3.5.0 (default, Sep 7 2015, 14:12:03)\n[GCC 4.8.4] on linux\nType \"help\", \"copyright\", \"credits\" or \"license\" for more information.\n---\nThis console is running in an asyncio event loop.\nIt allows you to wait for coroutines using the 'await' syntax.\nTry: await asyncio.sleep(1, result=3, loop=loop)\n---\n```\n\n```python3\n>>> await asyncio.sleep(1, result=3)\n# Wait one second...\n3\n>>>\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\nFind more examples in the [documentation] and the [example directory].\n\n## Limitations\n\nThe python console exposed by [aioconsole] is quite limited compared to modern consoles such as [IPython] or [ptpython]. Luckily, those projects gained greater asyncio support over the years. In particular, the following use cases overlap with [aioconsole] capabilities:\n\n- [Embedding a ptpython console in an asyncio program](https://github.com/prompt-toolkit/ptpython/blob/master/examples/asyncio-python-embed.py)\n- [Using the await syntax in an IPython console](https://ipython.readthedocs.io/en/stable/whatsnew/version7.html#autowait-asynchronous-repl)\n\n## Contact\n\nVincent Michel: <mailto:vxgmichel@gmail.com>\n\n(pypi)=\n\n[aioconsole]: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/aioconsole\n[argparse]: https://docs.python.org/dev/library/argparse.html\n[code.interact]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/code.html#code.interact\n[documentation]: http://aioconsole.readthedocs.io/\n[example directory]: https://github.com/vxgmichel/aioconsole/blob/master/example\n[exec]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#exec\n[github]: https://github.com/vxgmichel/aioconsole\n[input]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#input\n[ipython]: https://ipython.readthedocs.io\n[print]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#print\n[ptpython]: https://github.com/prompt-toolkit/ptpython\n[stream]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio-stream.html\n"], "modules": [{"name": "aioconsole.compat", "documentation": ["Compatibility helpers for the different Python versions."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "aioconsole.compat.platform", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command", "documentation": ["Provide an asynchronous equivalent to the python console."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli", "bases": ["console.AsynchronousConsole"], "methods": [{"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "commands", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "streams", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prog", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prompt_control", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "loop", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.get_default_banner", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.help_command", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reader", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "writer", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.list_command", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reader", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "writer", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.exit_command", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reader", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "writer", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.command.AsynchronousCli.runsource", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "aioconsole.events", "documentation": ["Provide an interactive event loop class."], "functions": [{"name": "aioconsole.events.set_interactive_policy", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "locals", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "banner", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "serve", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "prompt_control", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Use an interactive event loop by default."]}, {"name": "aioconsole.events.run_console", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": 